           ('02:00 PM', 'Monday', 1000, np.int64(2))]
context = [('12:00 PM', 'Monday', 1000, 2)]
result = predict_next_places(history, context)
print(result["prediction"]["place_ids"])
```

Please note that the output will be different every time you run the code as it depends on the random initialization of probabilities in the naive Bayes classifier.
